   <mods:abstract>Received Amherst's of 10 September. Some confusion in transmitting
            information regarding Van Alen's death and successor as Amherst's agent. Van Schaack's
            suggestion of Evert Van Alen as new agent, seconded by Jay. Jay regrets news of death of
            Mrs. Pinfold; wishes Amherst health. Jay himself: retired 1801 to paternal estate;
            blessed with 5 children; death of wife and son-in-law. Own health - "I am not very often
            sick, and yet seldom very well." Obliged to Amherst for assurance of welcome reception
            to those Jay might recommend.</mods:abstract>
